      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NEDS BEACH NZ (8) had to dig deep to salute at the most recent appearance over 1609m at Gawler, getting home by just a nose. Should enjoy a nice smother from this draw and will be looking for a split at some stage. Must raise the bar but he has the ability to test this field. BALLADORO (5) settled in the leading division then took control and kept finding to score narrowly over 1609m at Port Pirie six days ago. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. His last-start form is good enough to take out a race like this. MEET ME AT THE BEACH NZ (1) was out of the money two runs ago then broke and finished sixth last start over 1609m at Gawler, coming home 35 metres from the winner. It doesn't get any easier but she is talented enough to be competitive. TRIGGER (3) disappointed last time when eighth over 2070m at Gawler. Can do a lot better so worth considering.",
